session 5f technology and outsourcing cassandra robertson assistant professor of law case western reserve university organizat page 1 session 5f technology and outsourcing cassandra robertson assistant professor of law case western reserve university organizational behavior and international legal outsourcing abstract international outsourcing has come to the legal profession the aba has given international outsourcing its stamp of approval and an ailing economy has pushed both clients and firms to consider sending more legal work abroad a few recent articles have looked at the ethical implications of international outsourcing analyzing issues such as the supervision of foreign legal professionals confidentiality and conflicts of interest this article further develops that analysis by integrating research from the fields of organizational behavior and social psychology it identifies organizational pressures in the practice of law that affect how legal work is performed in a transnational context and it examines how individuals on both sides of the outsourcing process influence the success or failure of a globalized practice
